### Social Network Identity API - Test Login Endpoints
### Base URL (update if different)
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001
@identityUrl = https://localhost:7001

### ===========================================
### GET TEST USERS
### Get list of available test users for login testing
### ===========================================
GET {{identityUrl}}/api/login/test-users
Accept: application/json

### ===========================================
### HEALTH CHECK
### Check if the login service is healthy
### ===========================================
GET {{identityUrl}}/api/login/health
Accept: application/json

### ===========================================
### LOGIN - Admin User
### Simple login endpoint that returns OAuth token
### ===========================================
POST {{identityUrl}}/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### SAVE TOKEN from response
# Use this in subsequent requests

### ===========================================
### LOGIN - Regular User (John Doe)
### ===========================================
POST {{identityUrl}}/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "john.doe",
  "password": "password123"
}

### ===========================================
### LOGIN - Test User (Legacy)
### ===========================================
POST {{identityUrl}}/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "test",
  "password": "password"
}

### ===========================================
### LOGIN - Moderator User
### ===========================================
POST {{identityUrl}}/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "moderator",
  "password": "mod123"
}

### ===========================================
### LOGIN - Invalid Credentials (Should Fail)
### ===========================================
POST {{identityUrl}}/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "invalid",
  "password": "wrong"
}

### ===========================================
### OAUTH TOKEN ENDPOINT (Direct)
### Get token using OAuth 2.0 password grant
### ===========================================
POST {{identityUrl}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password
&username=admin
&password=admin123
&scope=openid profile email

### ===========================================
### USER INFO ENDPOINT
### Get user information using access token
### Replace {access_token} with actual token from login response
### ===========================================
@accessToken = YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

GET {{identityUrl}}/connect/userinfo
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### ===========================================
### CLIENT CREDENTIALS FLOW
### For service-to-service authentication
### ===========================================
POST {{identityUrl}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=client_credentials
&client_id=client_app
&client_secret=client_secret
&scope=openid profile

### ===========================================
### REFRESH TOKEN
### Get new access token using refresh token
### Replace {refresh_token} with actual refresh token from login response
### ===========================================
@refreshToken = YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE

POST {{identityUrl}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=refresh_token
&refresh_token={{refreshToken}}

### ===========================================
### TEST USERS SUMMARY
### ===========================================
# Available test users:
# 1. admin / admin123 - Admin user with full privileges
# 2. john.doe / password123 - Regular user
# 3. jane.smith / password123 - Regular user
# 4. test / password - Legacy test user
# 5. moderator / mod123 - Moderator with elevated privileges
